      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cudjoe_Key%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Henry Flagler’s Overseas Railroad, finished in 1912, linked the Lower Keys to the mainland, opening Cudjoe Key to modest farming and fishing.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Cudjoe_Key,_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Hurricane Irma struck Cudjoe Key as a Category 4 in 2017, leaving the island battered but still resilient.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14,
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Cudjoe_Key,_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Cudjoe Bay lies south of the island, while the Rattlesnake Lumps sit just northwest, marking the edge of tidal waters.",
